{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-template-js","path":"/make/oled-display-ssd1306","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>I have OLED monochrome display module 128x64 pixels blue color based on SSD1306 chip. It's can take 3.3V and 5V as well. We are going to connect it to Arduino UNO using I2C. Also I2C wil be shared with <a href=\"/make/temperature-sensor-rpi4\">the temperature sensor</a>.</p>\n<p>Just a few small tips that will save hours:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Find the original datasheet (especially for any <a href=\"https://s.click.aliexpress.com/e/_DcQKqy7\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">cheap clone</a>)</li>\n<li>Update ALL libraries. I <a href=\"https://learn.adafruit.com/monochrome-oled-breakouts/arduino-library-and-examples\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">installed</a> the latest Adafruit_GFX and <a href=\"https://github.com/adafruit/Adafruit_SSD1306\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Adafruit_SSD1306</a>, but it started working only after I updated other libraries (like <strong>Adafruit BusIO</strong>). All those defines are fragile.</li>\n<li>Don’t trust silkscreen labels. My display has a resistor that switches between <code class=\"language-text\">0x78</code> and <code class=\"language-text\">0x7A</code> I2C address acording to the silkscreen, but it uses address <code class=\"language-text\">0x3C</code></li>\n</ul>\n<p>About connection and short test example cannot say anything better than <a href=\"https://randomnerdtutorials.com/guide-for-oled-display-with-arduino/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">this tutorial</a></p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 650px; flex:0.9644970414201184;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/1c8d81867ac7f07324635752a2a66b2b/b78fc/oled-display-ssd1306.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 103.68098159509202%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"oled display ssd1306\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/1c8d81867ac7f07324635752a2a66b2b/6aca1/oled-display-ssd1306.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/1c8d81867ac7f07324635752a2a66b2b/d2f63/oled-display-ssd1306.jpg 163w,\n/static/1c8d81867ac7f07324635752a2a66b2b/c989d/oled-display-ssd1306.jpg 325w,\n/static/1c8d81867ac7f07324635752a2a66b2b/6aca1/oled-display-ssd1306.jpg 650w,\n/static/1c8d81867ac7f07324635752a2a66b2b/7c09c/oled-display-ssd1306.jpg 975w,\n/static/1c8d81867ac7f07324635752a2a66b2b/b78fc/oled-display-ssd1306.jpg 987w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h2 id=\"questions\" style=\"position:relative;\">Questions<a href=\"#questions\" aria-label=\"questions permalink\" class=\"with-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\">\n                <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3\n                3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3\n                  9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64\n                  1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\">\n                </path>\n                </svg></a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Does it require re